<br>
1) <b>Make sure you have backups of anything you care about</b>, including install disks for any programs you care about, and serial #s or other codes you need to unlock them.<br>
2) Actually reformatting is easy... get to a DOS prompt (should be on your start menu, but it would probably be better to shutdown using the "Restart in DOS mode" option), and c:\> format c: (assuming your hard drive is C, otherwise substitute the appropriate letter)<br>
3) Re-install Win98 (or whatever OS) and all your programs....  this takes a while... <br>
4) Copy the data you saved in the first step from the backups to the newly-formatted drive.<br>
<br>
I've done this, but not for quite a while, and mine had other complicating factors - please don't use these instructions without someone else posting that they seem reasonable.  I'm assuming you've got a fairly basic standard setup here, and I would really really hate to cause you problems cause I think I know more than I do.  <p><FONT face="Comic Sans MS" color="007fee"><font size=4>Kyrstellaine</FONT><br><font color="ffffff">
