<br>
Write down the model and version numbers of your video, sound and other accessory cards.  Find this under Control Panel... System.... Device manager.<br>
<br>
Write down the configuration of your network adapter or modem.<br>
<br>
Best bet - get a friend who knows their stuff in this arena.  Buy him/her a nice dinner and let them do the tricky part of getting your system up to a basic level of function again.<br>
