<br>
I'd suggest doing a search for any text documents (depending on what program you use, you'd want to look for *.doc, *.txt, *.wri, etc.) and image files, as these are usually the things you'll not be able to replace when you reinstall programs.  Also, check in your game(s) directories for Save files, and of course, back up those EQ files!  I always backup the client.ini and the character *.opt (I think that's right) files for the characters I'm actually using.<br>
<br>
When I nuke a system, I use a rescue disk.  You can create one of these by right-clicking on the Floppy drive icon in My Computer, and selecting Format.  There should be an option somewhere to make a rescue disk (not sure what Windows calls it though).  You can boot off that floppy into DOS, and format from there.<br>
<br>
When you format I recommend typing 'format /u c:' to wipe it clean.  Of course, that's prob'ly just me being paranoid and totally unnecessary, but it's the way I've formatted my drives for almost 5 years now.<br>
<br>
Finally, do allot at least 24 hours to bring your system back up to speed.  While everything should run smoothly and take  under 8 hours to nuke and rebuild, it never does.  There's always a driver that doesn't want to install or file you forgot to back up or something completely insane, like sudden resource conflicts even though you haven't TOUCHED the cards.<br>
<br>
